      "Yes, your **total heap is healthy**, but this crash is probably not about total heap.",
      "",
      "The key mismatch:",
      "",
      "- Your diagnostic uses `heap_caps_get_free_size(MALLOC_CAP_8BIT)`.",
      "- mDNS allocates with `MALLOC_CAP_INTERNAL | MALLOC_CAP_8BIT`.",
      "",
      "So `heap_free_min=4094440` is mostly telling us “PSRAM + internal 8-bit heap is fine.” It does **not** prove internal heap is fine.",
      "",
      "This stack is very specific:",
      "",
      "```text",
      "mdns_networking_lwip.c:176",
      "packet = mdns_mem_malloc(sizeof(mdns_rx_packet_t));",
      "if (!packet) HOOK_MALLOC_FAILED;",
      "```",
      "",
      "And `mdns_mem_malloc()` is:",
      "",
      "```c",
      "heap_caps_malloc(size, MDNS_MEMORY_CAPS)",
      "```",
      "",
      "Your framework config says:",
      "",
      "```c",
      "#define CONFIG_MDNS_MEMORY_ALLOC_INTERNAL 1",
      "```",
      "",
      "So mDNS failed to allocate a tiny `mdns_rx_packet_t` from **internal RAM**. Then the failure logger called `ESP_LOGE`, which tried to initialize/acquire a newlib stdio lock, and that also needed an internal FreeRTOS mutex. That second allocation failed and caused the abort at `locks.c:65`.",
      "",
      "So the likely story is:",
      "",
      "1. Browser/OS sends mDNS traffic while you load the page, probably `.local` discovery or background probing.",
      "2. mDNS receive callback runs in `tcpip_thread`.",
      "3. Internal-capable heap is exhausted or badly fragmented at that instant.",
      "4. mDNS allocation fails.",
      "5. The allocation-failure log path tries to allocate a stdio mutex.",
      "6. That fails too, so `abort()`.",
      "",
      "I’d add diagnostics for:",
      "",
      "```c",
      "heap_caps_get_free_size(MALLOC_CAP_INTERNAL | MALLOC_CAP_8BIT)",
      "heap_caps_get_minimum_free_size(MALLOC_CAP_INTERNAL | MALLOC_CAP_8BIT)",
